    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Poisson Regression\n",
        "\n",
        "Poisson regression is the GLM for **count data**: responses $Y_i \\in \\{0, 1, 2, \\ldots\\}$. A natural model is $Y_i \\sim \\text{Poisson}(\\lambda_i)$, with $\\mathbb{E}[Y_i] = \\lambda_i > 0$ and — crucially — $\\text{Var}(Y_i) = \\lambda_i$ (variance equals mean).\n",
        "\n",
        "We use the **log link** to ensure $\\lambda_i > 0$:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\\log \\lambda_i = \\mathbf{x}_i^\\top\\boldsymbol{\\beta}, \\quad \\text{so} \\quad \\lambda_i = e^{\\mathbf{x}_i^\\top\\boldsymbol{\\beta}}.$$\n",
        "\n",
        "Coefficients are interpreted multiplicatively via the **incidence rate ratio (IRR)** $e^{\\hat{\\beta}_j}$, the Poisson analogue of the odds ratio:\n",
        "\n",
        "| Coefficient | Interpretation |\n",
        "|---|---|\n",
        "| $\\beta_j$ | A one-unit increase in $X_j$ **adds** $\\beta_j$ to $\\log\\lambda$ |\n",
        "| $e^{\\beta_j}$ | A one-unit increase in $X_j$ **multiplies** $\\lambda$ by $e^{\\beta_j}$ |\n",
        "| $e^{\\beta_j} > 1$ | The expected count **increases** |\n",
        "| $e^{\\beta_j} < 1$ | The expected count **decreases** |\n",
        "\n",
        "### Application: Police Frisk Data"
      ],
      "id": "fc4d0ef4"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "frisk = pd.read_csv(\"data/frisk.txt\", sep=r\"\\s+\", skiprows=6)\n",
        "frisk.head()"
      ],
      "id": "93bc1021",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "X = (frisk\n",
        "    .groupby(['eth', 'precinct'])[[\"stops\", \"past.arrests\"]]\n",
        "    .sum()\n",
        "    .reset_index()\n",
        "    .pipe(pd.get_dummies, columns=['eth', 'precinct'], dtype=int)\n",
        "    .assign(intercept=1)  # Adds a column called 'intercept' with all values equal to 1.\n",
        "    .sort_values(by='stops')\n",
        "    .reset_index(drop=True)\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "y = X.pop(\"stops\")"
      ],
      "id": "fbb7c865",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "model_no_indicators = sm.GLM(\n",
        "    y,\n",
        "    X[\"intercept\"],\n",
        "    offset=np.log(X[\"past.arrests\"]),\n",
        "    family=sm.families.Poisson(),\n",
        ")\n",
        "result_no_indicators = model_no_indicators.fit()\n",
        "print(result_no_indicators.summary())"
      ],
      "id": "3f9c4d57",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "plt.plot(y, result_no_indicators.fittedvalues, 'o')\n",
        "plt.plot(y, y, '--', label='y = x')\n",
        "plt.ylabel(\"fitted value\")\n",
        "plt.xlabel(\"observed value\")\n",
        "plt.legend()\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ],
      "id": "8173bda6",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "model_with_ethnicity = sm.GLM(\n",
        "    y,\n",
        "    X[['intercept', 'eth_2', 'eth_3']],\n",
        "    offset=np.log(X[\"past.arrests\"]),\n",
        "    family=sm.families.Poisson(),\n",
        ")\n",
        "result_with_ethnicity = model_with_ethnicity.fit()\n",
        "print(result_with_ethnicity.summary())"
      ],
      "id": "180d3e22",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "model_with_ethnicity_and_precinct = sm.GLM(\n",
        "    y,\n",
        "    X.drop(columns=[\"eth_1\", \"precinct_1\", \"past.arrests\"]),\n",
        "    offset=np.log(X[\"past.arrests\"]),\n",
        "    family=sm.families.Poisson(),\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "result_with_ethnicity_and_precinct = model_with_ethnicity_and_precinct.fit()\n",
        "print(result_with_ethnicity_and_precinct.summary())"
      ],
      "id": "02248cac",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "precinct_coefs = result_with_ethnicity_and_precinct.params.iloc[2:-1] # Only intersted in precinct\n",
        "precinct_interval = result_with_ethnicity_and_precinct.conf_int().reindex(precinct_coefs.index)\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(15, 6))\n",
        "plt.plot(precinct_coefs, '.')\n",
        "for precinct, interval in precinct_interval.iterrows():\n",
        "    plt.plot([precinct, precinct], interval, color='C0')\n",
        "plt.axhline(y=0, linestyle=':', color='black')\n",
        "plt.xticks(\n",
        "    precinct_coefs.index[::3],\n",
        "    [int(x[1]) for x in precinct_coefs.index.str.split(\"_\",)][::3]\n",
        ")\n",
        "plt.ylabel(\"Estimated coefficient\")\n",
        "plt.xlabel(\"Precinct\")\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ],
      "id": "92dae92d",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "plt.figure(figsize=(15,6))\n",
        "plt.scatter(\n",
        "    y, result_with_ethnicity.fittedvalues, \n",
        "    marker='o', color='#fc8d62', edgecolors='white', \n",
        "    linewidths=0.4, s=60, label=\"with ethnicity\")\n",
        "plt.scatter(\n",
        "    y, result_with_ethnicity_and_precinct.fittedvalues, \n",
        "    marker='^', color='#8da0cb', edgecolors='white', \n",
        "    linewidths=0.4, s=60, label=\"with eth and precinct\")\n",
        "plt.plot(y, y, '--', color='black', label='y = x')\n",
        "plt.ylabel(\"fitted value\")\n",
        "plt.xlabel(\"observed value\")\n",
        "plt.legend()\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ],
      "id": "93d176a8",
